The Government can blame local residents for “partying” all it likes, and I’m not ruling out that some cases arose because of a small number of irresponsible people, but it feels abundantly clear what has happened here. Yet again, working class cities are being demonised.

West Yorkshire, Leeds included, has a high working class population. With many residents forced to work throughout the pandemic in essential jobs and with some employers potentially not enforcing hygiene measures, these workers are vulnerable to COVID.

It’s been a few days since the Leeds Lockdown was announced. As a resident of Leeds, it still feels deeply unsettling that the narrative seems to be that irresponsible locals and partying students contributed to the rise in cases. It is abundantly clear that this is not true.

The amount of ridiculous diet trends I have seen on TikTok is staggering. I worry that my thirteen-year-old sister, who uses TikTok religiously, might see this discourse and believe that it is what she should be doing.

TikTok is extremely popular with teenage girls, and this specific cohort is particularly susceptible to the idea that they should be “skinny”. The amount of toxic diet content I come across, when this is not a registered interest of mine, is shocking. It is so harmful.

T/W: Food, weight. You know what I would like to stop seeing on TikTok? Videos documenting a person’s 1000-calorie diet and exercise plan. NO ONE, not even a seven-year-old, should be eating as little as 1000 calories. No one.

Remember that herd immunity policy that the Government U-turned on? Remember its premature change in message from "stay at home" to "stay alert"? This Government does not care about the British public. It's defence of Cummings is symbolic of that.

Day in, day out, the British media push the blame for the spread of COVID-19 onto the public by publishing images of busy London parks. Truly, the blame lies with the British Government which failed to act properly to stop the spread of COVID-19 back in March.

The lockdown rules disallow travel between residences. You simply cannot move from one to the other. It is an insult to the British public to pretend that Cummings' actions were legal. It is also a manipulation of the truth to deny that the police were notified. #sackcummings

The most outrageous thing about all of this, though, is that 10 Downing Street is trying to argue that Cummings did not breach lockdown rules. At this point, it was essential travel only. This simply does not constitute an essential journey.
Not to mention the fact that his child was possibly carrying COVID-19, and could have passed it onto family members.

At home, we have soap, but how is my little brother supposed to protect himself out and about at school? He tells me the soap dispensers are constantly broken at his secondary school, vandalised by pupils. At Luton airport yesterday, sanitiser dispensers were empty.

She cannot find any in the supermarkets or in the pharmacies. We’ve run out of the sanitiser we had on hand before this crisis. I hope everyone who is selfishly hoarding unnecessary amounts of essential resources considers the damage they will do to vulnerable people.
